<h2><a name="Tour highlights"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Tour highlights</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Spend a week exploring the best parts of Eastern Canada</li>
<li>Enjoy a guided tour of the cosmopolitan city of Toronto</li>
<li>Take a trip to the world-famous Niagara Falls</li>
<li>Admire the UNESCO waterways of Ottawa</li>
<li>Discover the picturesque cities of Quebec and Montreal</li>
<li>Optional whale watching excursion from Quebec (payable locally)</li>
<li>Experienced and knowledgeable tour manager throughout</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-canada/eastern-journey-escorted-tour#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Itinerary"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Itinerary</span></h2>
<p><strong>Day 1: UK to Toronto</strong></p>
<p>Arrive into Toronto’s Pearson International Airport and transfer independently to your downtown hotel. The rest of the day is free for you to explore and after checking in with your tour director we recommend heading out to explore the dynamic streets of Toronto. Experience the colorful neighborhoods, attractions or sample the cuisine in one of the many local restaurants.</p>
<p><strong>Day 2: Toronto / Niagara Falls Excursion</strong></p>
<p>This morning meet your fellow travelers at breakfast before setting out to discover more of Canada’s most cosmopolitan city. There will be plenty of time to see the provincial parliament buildings, waterfront, impressive CN Tower and lively Chinatown. Afterwards you'll leave the city skyline behind and head for the Niagara Peninsula, passing through outlying communities and towns along the shores of Lake Ontario en route to the spectacular Niagara Falls.<span> </span><span>Admire the geological wonder in your own time or take the "Voyage to the Falls" boat cruise, which passes all three waterfalls - the American Falls, Bridal Veil Falls &amp; Horseshoe Falls (approx.$30 per person - payable locally).</span></p>
<p><span>Meals included: Breakfast</span></p>
<p><strong>Day 3: Toronto to Ottawa</strong></p>
<p>Today we drive east towards the national capital city of Ottawa. Winding through rolling farmland and following the rivers and lakes of the Rideau Waterway, you'll arrive in Ottawa to enjoy a sightseeing tour. The city offers many great sights including the government buildings on Parliament Hill, Byward Market, City Hall and the Rideau Canal (designated by UNESCO as a World Heritage Site).</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 4: Ottawa to Quebec City</strong></p>
<p>The French-speaking province of Quebec is your next stop on this tour. Travelling along the scenic Ottawa River and skirting the magnificent Laurentians you'll arrive in the cultural heartland of Quebec City. <span>Bask in the charm as you stroll through the old city and take in over 400 years of history in the birthplace of French North America. The ornate city gates, Lower Town, the Citadel and Battlefields Park are highlights of the tour.</span></p>
<p><span>Meals included: Breakfast</span></p>
<p><strong>Day 5: Quebec City</strong></p>
<p>A day at your leisure to further explore the sights of this charming World Heritage Site. An optional full day excursion will see you board a regular boat and search for the worlds largest mammals on an exciting whale watching experience. Journey along the beautiful St. Lawrence River, which is home to number of different species of whale. The day ends with a trip to the spectacular Montmorency Falls that surpass the world-famous Niagara falls in height. Spend the evening strolling around the city, the Château Frontenac.(Whale watching Tour &amp; Montmorency Falls - approx. $126 per person - payable locally)</p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 6: Quebec City to Montreal</strong></p>
<p>Today you depart Quebec City and follow the St.Lawrence River en route to Montreal. The dynamic city of Montreal is the second-largest French-speaking city in the world and encapsulates the two founding cultures of Canada boasting a curious blend of history and modernity. Touring the downtown area we view the Olympic Complex, charming Old Montreal, McGill University, the residential streets of Mount Royal and the bustling shopping streets. </p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 7: Montreal to Toronto</strong></p>
<p>Stopping off in Rockport you'll have the opportunity to cruise the 1000 islands on an optional excursion. Discover this well kept jewel of the St. Lawrence River with several rugged islands and chic communities (approx. $26 per person - payable locally). After loop back to Toronto, where you'll have time to explore the colourful neighbourhoods and diverse city streets. </p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p><strong>Day 8: Toronto to UK</strong></p>
<p><span>Bid Canada farewell before some last minute shopping for souvenirs to remember your amazing trip. Individually transfer to </span>Toronto’s Pearson International Airport in time to check in for your return flight.  </p>
<p>Meals included: Breakfast</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-canada/eastern-journey-escorted-tour#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Your holiday includes"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Your holiday includes</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Return flights from the UK</li>
<li>Transportation by modern tour coach with experienced tour driver and tour director throughout.</li>
<li>7 night accommodation in 3 star hotels or similar</li>
<li>7 breakfasts</li>
<li>City/town tours in Montreal, Ottawa, Quebec and Toronto</li>
<li>Niagara Falls excursion</li>
</ul>
<p><span></span><strong>Your holiday excludes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Airport transfers in Toronto (Day 1 &amp; Day 8)</li>
<li>All excursions marked 'optional'</li>
<li>Any extras, drinks, gratuities and personal expenses</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: right;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-canada/eastern-journey-escorted-tour#Tour highlights">[Back to top]</a></p>
<h2><a name="Hotels"></a><span class="geolocation-title">Hotels</span></h2>
<p><strong>★★★ Courtyard by Marriott, Toronto (2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★ Capital Hill Hotel &amp; Suites or Best Western Plus Ottawa Downtown, Ottawa (1 night)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★ Hotel Ambassadeur, Travelodge Quebec or Hotel Lindbergh, </strong><strong>Quebec City </strong><strong>(2 nights)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★ Hotel Faubourg Montreal, Hotel Chrome or Lelux Hotel, Montreal (1 night)</strong></p>
<p><strong>★★★ Hilton Garden Inn or Courtyard by Marriott Toronto Airport, Toronto (1 night)</strong></p>
<p><span>Please note that if any of the above are not available, they will be changed to hotels of a similar standard and location. </span><span>If you'd like to extend your stay, please call us to add a pre- or post-departure hotel in Toronto.</span></p>
